<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="sans-serif" COLOR="#FFFFFF"><b>xearo</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF"><B></B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Joined: May 29, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Posts: 46</FONT></td><TD><img src="/forum/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="sans-serif" SIZE="1" COLOR="#FFFFFF">Posted: 2001-06-05 11:04&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" face="sans-serif">When we patch tomorrow (6-5-01), we will be introducing code on Rallos Zek server that will result in faction hits similar to those on the team servers. <BR>Killing a character in any of their races home town will cause you to take a faction hit. This counts for all home cities. So, if you kill a Human in any of the city zones of Qeynos (or Freeport, or Surefall Glade), you will suffer a faction hit, even if that Human was born in Freeport. All of Greater Faydark is the starting city for Wood Elves. There will also be faction hits for killing High Elves and Half-Elves in Greater Faydark. Killing an Erudite in either Paineel or Erudin will cause a faction hit. <BR><BR>Also, for those of you trying to start or complete quests for King Tormax, you need to know that we've made a change. You will now need to be in good standing with him in order to do his quests. In game terms, this means you will need to be at least amiable. <BR><BR>Alan <BR></FONT><BR>
