<FONT COLOR="#FFFFFF" face="sans-serif">Problem with aggressor flags is this (for example):<BR>Ganker04 attacks Goodie08.  Goodie01 and Goodie02 don't like Ganker04 so much, so they decide to help their good budy, Goodie08.  Do Goodie01 and Goodie02 get factions hits when they kill Ganker04?  If so, how is that fair?<BR><BR>One of the wonderful things about Rallos Zek is the ability to retaliate for flagrant play.  If someone tries to hurt my friend, you can hunt him down.  Aggressor flags penalize anti-PK's for retaliating against attacks.  It wouldn't just be as simple as implementing aggressor flags to solve the problem.  They need to find some alternate solution.  I think the faction hits in cities is pretty much a waste of their time.  It won't solve anything except newbie ganking, which sanctuary levels should have already taken care of, for the most part.<BR><BR>Just my thoughts, take 'em or leave 'em!<BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: Alchemy on 2001-06-05 21:31 ]</font></FONT><BR>
